{
  "text": "Near the top of the Gabardiella section, a large, wide and flat species of Nummulites, Nummulites millecaput is observed (F5d). This species of Nummulites characterizes deep and calm environments, at the lower limit of the photic zone (Beavington-Penney and [CITATION_1] In the Argu\u00eds area, the upper part of the section is comprised of silty wackstones with large Nummulites (F5e), overlain by fine wackstones with red algae debris and some coral fragments (F5f). It is hard to give a precise depth of deposition for these facies, but by comparison with the contemporaneous deposits of the Guara Limestones in the Belsu\u00e9 syncline, we can propose that they were deposited in an outer ramp environment.",
